cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing intelligent agents that interact with humans in complex interaction scenarios. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper deals with processing human affective behavior in storytelling. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the dataset consists of videos of interactions. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a baseline for evaluating models for affective processing tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses different evaluation protocols and a baseline for training models.
